author: COMSOL
description: Magnetotellurics is a method for estimating the resistivity profile of Earth's subsurface using the natural electromagnetic source provided by the ionosphere. This example is a COMSOL implementation of the standard magnetotellurics benchmark model COMMEMI-3D-2 defined by Zhdanov and others.
